=====================================================================
CURSOR TASK SPEC — GITHUB RELEASES UPDATE SYSTEM (STORE-FREE)
=====================================================================

ROLE
You are acting as a senior platform engineer and release engineer.
Your responsibility is to implement a complete, reliable update system
for an app distributed via GitHub Releases (NOT App Store / Play Store).

The system must be silent when up to date and visible when action is required.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
GOAL
---------------------------------------------------------------------
When a new version is published on GitHub Releases:

• The app detects it automatically
• Compares installed version vs latest release
• Notifies the user (optional or forced)
• Provides a correct platform download link
• Never spams the user
• Never crashes when offline
• Works for macOS, Windows, and Android TV APK distribution

---------------------------------------------------------------------
SOURCE OF TRUTH (LOCKED)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
GitHub Releases is the ONLY source of truth.

Use GitHub REST API:
GET https://api.github.com/repos/{OWNER}/{REPO}/releases/latest

Do NOT scrape HTML pages.
Do NOT hardcode version numbers.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
EXPECTED RELEASE FORMAT (REQUIRED)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Each GitHub Release MUST include:

• tag_name: "v1.5.0"   (semantic version)
• body: release notes (markdown allowed)
• assets:
  - macOS:  *.dmg  or *.zip
  - Windows: *.exe or *.msi
  - Android TV: *.apk

OPTIONAL (RECOMMENDED):
• Release body includes flags:
  FORCE_UPDATE=true
  MIN_SUPPORTED_VERSION=1.4.0

---------------------------------------------------------------------
VERSION CHECK FLOW (MANDATORY)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Trigger update check:
   • On app cold launch (Splash / Bootstrap)
   • On app resume IF last check > 24 hours

2) Fetch latest release metadata from GitHub API.

3) Parse:
   • latestVersion = tag_name
   • releaseNotes = body
   • assets = assets[]

4) Compare with local app version.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
VERSION COMPARISON RULES
---------------------------------------------------------------------
If currentVersion == latestVersion:
→ App is up to date
→ DO NOTHING (no UI, no notification)

If currentVersion < MIN_SUPPORTED_VERSION:
→ FORCE UPDATE
→ Block app usage
→ Show mandatory update screen

If currentVersion < latestVersion:
→ OPTIONAL UPDATE
→ Show non-blocking notification/modal

---------------------------------------------------------------------
UPDATE UI RULES
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Optional Update:
• Shown once per version
• Can be dismissed
• Includes:
  - version number
  - release notes
  - “Update Now” button

Forced Update:
• Cannot be dismissed
• Blocks navigation
• Only action: “Update Now”
• App remains unusable until updated

UI must match app branding.
No default alert dialogs unless styled.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
PLATFORM ASSET SELECTION (REQUIRED)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
From GitHub release assets, select download URL by platform:

macOS:
• Prefer .dmg, fallback to .zip

Windows:
• Prefer .exe or .msi

Android TV:
• Prefer .apk

If platform asset is missing:
• Show error message
• Do NOT crash
• Log diagnostic info

---------------------------------------------------------------------
DOWNLOAD & INSTALL BEHAVIOR
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Desktop (macOS / Windows):
• Clicking “Update Now” opens browser to asset URL
• OR downloads in-app if already supported
• App may request restart after install (optional)

Android TV:
• Clicking “Update Now” opens download intent
• OR launches installer if permissions allow
• Gracefully handle install permissions failure

NO silent auto-install without user intent.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
STATE & SPAM PREVENTION (REQUIRED)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Persist locally:
• lastCheckedAt
• lastNotifiedVersion

Rules:
• Do NOT show same update notification twice
• Do NOT re-fetch more than once per 24h unless forced
• Do NOT notify again until a newer version exists

---------------------------------------------------------------------
OFFLINE & FAILURE HANDLING
---------------------------------------------------------------------
If GitHub API fails:
• Skip update check silently
• App must continue normally
• No error popups

If API rate-limited:
• Back off
• Retry next launch window

---------------------------------------------------------------------
SECURITY & SAFETY RULES
---------------------------------------------------------------------
• Do NOT embed GitHub tokens unless required
• If token is used:
  - store in env
  - never hardcode
• Validate version strings
• Never execute downloaded binaries automatically
• Never trust remote metadata blindly

---------------------------------------------------------------------
LOGGING (DEBUG ONLY)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Log:
• update check started
• update check skipped (cooldown)
• version comparison result
• update required / optional

Logs must NOT expose tokens or URLs with secrets.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
FILES TO ADD / MODIFY
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Client:
• UpdateService (GitHub API fetch + logic)
• VersionComparator utility
• UpdateModal / ForcedUpdateScreen
• Bootstrap/Splash integration

Optional:
• ReleaseNotes screen

---------------------------------------------------------------------
FINAL ACCEPTANCE CHECKLIST
---------------------------------------------------------------------
[ ] App fetches latest GitHub release
[ ] App skips all UI when up to date
[ ] Optional updates notify once per version
[ ] Forced updates block app correctly
[ ] Correct platform asset is selected
[ ] Offline mode works without issues
[ ] No notification spam
[ ] No crashes or weird handlers
[ ] Update UX matches app branding

If ANY item fails, fix before finalizing.
=====================================================================
END TASK
